'''Conversion coatings''' are [[coating]]s for metals where the part‘s surface is subjected to a chemical or electro-chemical process by the coating material which converts it into a decorative or protective substance. Examples include [[chromate conversion coating]]s, [[phosphate conversion coating]]s, [[Bluing (steel)|bluing]], [[black oxide]] coatings on steel, and [[anodizing]]. They are used for corrosion protection, to add decorative color and as paint primers.<ref>http://www.rit.edu/affiliate/nysp2i/sites/rit.edu.affiliate.nysp2i/files/pdfs/plating_or_conversion_coatings_final2e.pdf</ref><ref>http://core.materials.ac.uk/repository/eaa/talat/5202.pdf</ref><ref>http://www.electrochemsci.org/papers/vol3/3090993.pdf</ref>
