A '''Hiboy''' is a specialized, high-clearance type of farm [[tractor]] designed to operate in high crops without damaging them.  The largest producer of hiboys is [[Hagie Manufacturing|Hagie Manufacturing Company]] of [[Clarion, Iowa]], United States.  The most common uses of hiboys are for [[detasseling]], spraying herbicides, and applying [[glyphosate]] directly to weeds growing above crop height with a wick or wiper.

